<topicdoc>
<name> H+ - DefinitionPB1 </name>
<label> Definition </label>
<content>

H+ is the hydrogen ion concentration in blood. 

</content>
</topicdoc>

<topicdoc>
<name> H+ - Physical Units </name>
<label> Physical Units </label>
<content>

Units for H+ are Eq/L

</content>
</topicdoc>

<topicdoc>
<name> H+ - Concentration Units </name>
<label> Concentration Units </label>
<content>

Normal values for H+ are as follows:
Arterial Blood: 40nEq/L 
Venous Blood: 42nEq/L
Cell: 100nEq/L

